Our main result is that the host galaxy gas provides a luminosity-independent
 obscurer, for which we compute covering fractions.
 This obscurer does not provide Compton-thick columns, but large covering
 fractions (
\begin_inset Formula $40-90\%$
\end_inset

) at 
\begin_inset Formula $\NH>10^{22}\,{\rm cm}^{-2}$
\end_inset

.
