\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Marconi2004"

\end_inset

.
 The mass-dependence is defined by the 
\begin_inset Formula $\AP$
\end_inset

 parameter: at 
\begin_inset Formula $\AP=0$
\end_inset

, the PuffedTorus is mass-independent, corresponding to a strict luminosity-depe
ndent unified model, while at 
\begin_inset Formula $\AP=1$
\end_inset

 it is only Eddington-rate dependent.
 The parameters 
\begin_inset Formula $\AP$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{L43}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

 are not known apriori.
 For mass-scaling, 
\begin_inset Formula $\AP=2/3$
\end_inset

 is suggested from the theoretical works on the obscurer by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Elitzur2016"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Wada2015"

\end_inset

, however a wide range (e.g.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\AP=0-2$
\end_inset

) may be considered 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
before "see also"
key "Hoenig2007"

\end_inset

.
 We derive fiducial values for the other two parameters using the Swift/BAT
